INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('arrow', '[에로우]\n화살, 화살표', 'An arrow is a long thin weapon which is sharp and pointed at one end and which often has feathers at the other end. An arrow is shot from a bow.\nAn arrow is a written or printed sign that consists of a straight line with another line bent at a sharp angle at one end. This is a printed arrow: . The arrow points in a particular direction to indicate where something is.\n', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('arson', '[아r-슨]\n방화(죄)', 'Arson is the crime of deliberately setting fire to a building or vehicle.\n', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('art', '[아r-t]\n미술, 예술, 기술', 'Art consists of paintings, sculpture, and other pictures or objects which are created for people to look at and admire or think deeply about.\nArt is the activity or educational subject that consists of creating paintings, sculptures, and other pictures or objects for people to look at and admire or think deeply about.\nThe arts are activities such as music, painting, literature, cinema, and dance, which people can take part in for enjoyment, or to create works which express serious meanings or ideas of beauty.\nAt a university or college, arts are subjects such as history, literature, or languages in contrast to scientific subjects.\nIf you describe an activity as an art, you mean that it requires skill and that people learn to do it by instinct or experience, rather than by learning facts or rules.\n', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('artery', '[아r-더뤼]\n동맥, 간선 수로, 도로', 'Arteries are the tubes in your body that carry blood from your heart to the rest of your body. Compare vein.\nYou can refer to an important main route within a complex road, railway, or river system as an artery.\n', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('arthritis', '[어-쓰롸이디s]\n관절염', 'Arthritis is a medical condition in which the joints in someone''s body are swollen and painful.\n', 0, '2016-11-03');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('arthropod', '[아쓰러팟]\n절지동물 (거미, 게 등)', 'any invertebrate of the phylum Arthropoda, having jointed limbs, a segmented body, and an exoskeleton made of chitin. The group includes the crustaceans, insects, arachnids, and centipedes\n', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('article', '[아-뤼끌]\n(신물, 잡지의) 글, 기사, \n(합의서, 계약서의) 조항, \n~을 고발하다\n기사, 조항, 관사', 'An article is a piece of writing that is published in a newspaper or magazine.\nYou can refer to objects as articles of some kind.\nAn article of a formal agreement or document is a section of it which deals with a particular point.\nSomeone who is in articles is being trained as a lawyer or accountant by a firm with whom they have a written agreement.\nIn grammar, an article is a kind of determiner. In English, ''a'' and ''an'' are called the indefinite article, and ''the'' is called the definite article.\nIf you describe something as the genuine article, you are emphasizing that it is genuine, and often that it is very good.\n', 0, '2016-11-03');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('artifact', '[아릐풱t]\n(천연물과 대비하여) 인공물, 공예품, 유물\n인공 유물, 만들어낸 것', '', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('artificial', '[아뤼^핏셜]\n인공의, 인위적인, 인조의', 'artificial / synthetic / false / man-made / fake / imitation\nArtificial objects, materials, or processes do not occur naturally and are created by human beings, for example using science or technology.\nAn artificial state or situation exists only because someone has created it, and therefore often seems unnatural or unnecessary.\nIf you describe someone or their behaviour as artificial, you disapprove of them because they pretend to have attitudes and feelings which they do not really have.\n', 0, '2016-11-09');
