INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('department', '[디^파r-t먼t]\n(정부, 기업체, 대학 등과 같은 조직의 한) 부서,  학과', 'A department is one of the sections in an organization such as a government, business, or university. A department is also one of the sections in a large shop.\nIf you say that a task or area of knowledge is not your department, you mean that you are not responsible for it or do not know much about it.\n', 0, '2016-10-14');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('department store', '백화점', 'A department store is a large shop which sells many different kinds of goods.\nI recently went to a department store to shop for some shoes.\n', 0, '2016-11-10');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('departure', '[디^파r-춰r]\n출발, 떠남, 이탈, 사임\n(항공기, 기차 등의) 출발(편)\n(정도, 일상 등으로부터) 벗어남, 일탈', 'Departure or a departure is the act of going away from somewhere.\nThe departure of a person from a job, or a member from an organization, is their act of leaving it or being forced to leave it.\nIf someone does something different or unusual, you can refer to their action as a departure.\n', 0, '2016-11-10');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('departure to', '~로의 출발/출국', '', 0, '2016-08-31');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('depend', '[디^펜d]\n의존하다, 의지하다, \n믿다, 신뢰하다\n~나름이다, ~에 달려있다, 좌우되다\n매달리다, 종속하다', 'If you say that one thing depends on another, you mean that the first thing will be affected or determined by the second.\nIf you depend on someone or something, you need them in order to be able to survive physically, financially, or emotionally.\nIf you can depend on a person, organization, or law, you know that they will support you or help you when you need them.\nYou use depend in expressions such as it depends to indicate that you cannot give a clear answer to a question because the answer will be affected or determined by other factors.\n', 0, '2016-10-03');
INSERT INTO WORDS VALUES ('depend on', '~에 따라, 달렸다, 의존/의지하다', 'It depends on the kind of hawk. Some hawks eat fish some eat rodents. Hey we''re running out of light.\n"That''s what Merlin must have meant when he said the future of Camelot depends on us," said Annie.\nB : Well, that all depends on the traffic.\nDonna: It depends on the favor, but tell me anyway.\n', 0, '2016-11-23');
